genesis_payload.toml:275:"src/bottom_white/cas/store.rs" = "723dadf6dc824b2de37be55cf599d2fedf75ff4ea588be51b549e5eb2d71aff3"  # rehashed by Stage A3 / HEAD_t C2 R3 (2026-05-08; charter STAGE_A3_HEAD_T_C2_charter_2026-05-07.md FR-A3-HEAD-T-C2.2 / SG-A3.3): CasStore::put now invokes Git2LedgerWriter::advance_chaintape_cas_to(repo_path, git_oid, ...) after durable sidecar append, advancing refs/chaintape/cas to track each new CAS blob OID. Best-effort (`let _ = ...`) so a transient ref-update failure does NOT roll back the durable CAS write — the ref is overwrite-safe (force=true) and recovers on the next put. Pure additive; no change to put/get/open semantics. Class 3 surface (cas/store.rs is NOT in CLAUDE.md STEP_B restricted list — only cas/schema.rs is). Predecessor 2026-05-07 list_all_cids hash 687a6144 superseded.  # re-rehashed 2026-05-07 to add TRACE_MATRIX FC1-N34 + FC1-N35 doc-comment backlink to list_all_cids (per R-022 pre-commit hook). Predecessor strict-audit-fix hash e5d0c020 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-C0 strict-audit FC1-INV6 fix (2026-05-07; STRICT_AUDIT_TBC0_TAPE_2026-05-07.md Finding D): NEW pub fn `list_all_cids(&self) -> Vec<Cid>` — sibling to list_cids_by_object_type (R5) / count_by_object_type (R4). Returns every Cid in the in-memory index regardless of object_type. Used by audit_assertions::assert_50_cas_bytes_match_cids to walk all CAS objects + re-hash bytes against stored CIDs (closes the flip_cas_byte detection hole revealed on P05's tape). Pure-additive helper; no disk I/O; no change to put/get/open semantics. Class 3 surface (cas/store.rs is NOT in CLAUDE.md STEP_B restricted list — only cas/schema.rs is). Predecessor TB-18R R5 hash e6729db5 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R5 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R5_preflight_audit_extension.md §3 + §2.1): NEW pub fn `list_cids_by_object_type(&self, ty: ObjectType) -> Vec<Cid>` — sibling to count_by_object_type (R4). Returns the list of Cids for CAS objects whose metadata 