+"experiments/minif2f_v4/src/bin/evaluator.rs" = "3121069080f8119ec59392dbe7260676893a134d808d69bca2c285d2128cae5b"  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 R2 race fix (2026-05-11; Codex G2 R1 Q8 VETO closure): both EventResolve emit hooks (full-proof ~line 2823 + per-tactic ~line 3515) now NEST inside the existing `if let Some(vid) = verify_tx_id.clone()` block (was: emit happened unconditionally AFTER the block). New call shape passes `&vid` as the 3rd arg to `tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize` so the adapter helper can poll `claims_t[claim_id].status == Finalized` before EventResolve construction (prevents stale `parent_state_root` → StaleParent L4.E). Nesting also tightens the semantics: B2 emit only fires on a real OMEGA-Confirm + FinalizeReward path; previously the emit fired even on paths without `verify_tx_id` (no-op via adapter's `task_markets_t.state != Open` early-out, but semantically loose). Predecessor TB-N2 B2 R1 hash 09af8844 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 (2026-05-11; charter §3 B2 + gap audit §3.3 closure): added 2 NEW EventResolve emit hooks in OMEGA-Confirm exit paths (full-proof ~line 2823 + per-tactic ~line 3515). Each constructs `b2_task_id = TaskId(format!("task-{run_id}"))` and calls `turingosv4::runtime::adapter::tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize(&bundle.sequencer, b2_task_id, 5000)` after `tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify`. Best-effort poll-then-emit; failures non-fatal. Closes CPMM lifecycle gap: pre-B2 `TaskMarketState::Finalized` WRITE 0 sites; post-B2 OMEGA-Confirm path flips Open → Finalized making TB-13 CompleteSetRedeem reachable. Predecessor TB-N1 A4 hash ced49f42 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A4 (2026-05-10; session #36; charter §2 atom A4 + forward §8 grant): added `verify_peer` tool dispatch arm in `match action.tool.as_str()` between "post" and "step". Reads `action.target_work_tx_id` (required), `action.verdict` ("confirm"/"deny"/missing-defaults-Confirm), `action.bond_micro` (with A3-style saturating `