-"src/runtime/adapter.rs" = "18bc199e41859c1facec8e90889a39787af0deace01258ae530a89dc8a7c6c2d"  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 (2026-05-11): added `tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize` poll-then-emit helper (mirrors `tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify` pattern). Polls `q_snapshot` until task_markets_t[task_id].state == Open; emits `SystemEmitCommand::EventResolve` via `Sequencer::emit_system_tx`. Best-effort contract: Ok(true) on emit / Ok(false) on poll-budget-expiry or task already resolved / Err on unexpected emit_system_tx error. Closes the CPMM lifecycle automation gap from the OMEGA-Confirm exit path. Predecessor hash 48da399a superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.3 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.3 — CompleteSetRedeem env-var trigger): ADDITIVE — added make_real_complete_set_redeem_signed_by(keypairs, parent_state_root, event_task, owner, outcome, share_units, suffix, timestamp_logical) helper. Mirrors make_real_complete_set_mint_signed_by shape: builds CompleteSetRedeemTx + canonical-digest + agent-sign via AgentKeypairRegistry. Sole caller is the FORCE_REDEEM env-var hook in evaluator.rs (TB-16.x.2.3); no production caller wired yet. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.2.fix.r2 Patch F4 hash c1360a73 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.2.fix.r2 Patch F4 (2026-05-05; doc-only follow-up addressing Codex CHALLENGE E.3 from the .fix Class 3 audit): the prior .fix Patch E docstring referenced a nonexistent `Sequencer::set_current_round_for_test` symbol while explaining the time-unit difference between this helper and tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible. Patch F4 corrects the doc to point at the actual in-tree mutator (the `seed_q_for_challenge` test helper at src/state/sequencer.rs:~4185) and clarifies that no production round-advance mechanism is wired yet. NO behavior change — pure docstring edit; helper signature, eligibility logic, and call surface are unchanged from .fix Patch E. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.2.fix Patch E hash 3e770c4b superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.2