   164	"experiments/minif2f_v4/src/bin/evaluator.rs" = "3121069080f8119ec59392dbe7260676893a134d808d69bca2c285d2128cae5b"  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 R2 race fix (2026-05-11; Codex G2 R1 Q8 VETO closure): both EventResolve emit hooks (full-proof ~line 2823 + per-tactic ~line 3515) now NEST inside the existing `if let Some(vid) = verify_tx_id.clone()` block (was: emit happened unconditionally AFTER the block). New call shape passes `&vid` as the 3rd arg to `tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize` so the adapter helper can poll `claims_t[claim_id].status == Finalized` before EventResolve construction (prevents stale `parent_state_root` → StaleParent L4.E). Nesting also tightens the semantics: B2 emit only fires on a real OMEGA-Confirm + FinalizeReward path; previously the emit fired even on paths without `verify_tx_id` (no-op via adapter's `task_markets_t.state != Open` early-out, but semantically loose). Predecessor TB-N2 B2 R1 hash 09af8844 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 (2026-05-11; charter §3 B2 + gap audit §3.3 closure): added 2 NEW EventResolve emit hooks in OMEGA-Confirm exit paths (full-proof ~line 2823 + per-tactic ~line 3515). Each constructs `b2_task_id = TaskId(format!("task-{run_id}"))` and calls `turingosv4::runtime::adapter::tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize(&bundle.sequencer, b2_task_id, 5000)` after `tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify`. Best-effort poll-then-emit; failures non-fatal. Closes CPMM lifecycle gap: pre-B2 `TaskMarketState::Finalized` WRITE 0 sites; post-B2 OMEGA-Confirm path flips Open → Finalized making TB-13 CompleteSetRedeem reachable. Predecessor TB-N1 A4 hash ced49f42 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A4 (2026-05-10; session #36; charter §2 atom A4 + forward §8 grant): added `verify_peer` tool dispatch arm in `match action.tool.as_str()` between "post" and "step". Reads `action.target_work_tx_id` (required), `action.verdict` ("confirm"/"deny"/missing-defaults-Confirm), `action.bond_micro` (with A3-style saturating `i64::try_from(u).unwrap_or(i64::MAX)` cast + env fallback `TURINGOS_CHAINTAPE_VERIFY_BOND_MICRO` defaults 1000). Calls `make_real_verifytx_signed_by` and submits via `bus.submit_typed_tx`. FAIL-CLOSED `std::process::exit(3)` on q_snapshot or signing failure; FAIL-OPEN warn-and-skip in legacy mode (no chaintape). Closes the verify-peer agency layer per CLAUDE.md §13 verify/bond + Art. I.1.1 multi-agent verification. Predecessor TB-N1-A3 R2 hash afde6670 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A3 R2 Codex Q4 fix (2026-05-10; session #36; PRE-§8 dual audit R1 Codex CHALLENGE Q4): 3 OMEGA callsites' `u as i64` casts replaced with `i64::try_from(u).unwrap_or(i64::MAX)` saturating cast. Pre-fix `u as i64` would WRAP NEGATIVE if agent submitted `stake_micro > i64::MAX` (≈ 9.2 quintillion μC; theoretically possible via JSON injection though no real agent will), routing to `StakeInsufficient` (Step-4a `<= 0`) instead of the intended `StakeBalanceExceeded` (Step-4b `> balance`). Saturating-to-i64::MAX preserves fail-closed admission: u64 overflow → i64::MAX which always exceeds any agent balance (max realistic 30M μC) → fires StakeBalanceExceeded as Codex Q4 demanded. Pure-defensive fix; no protocol-wire-shape change; no sequencer change. Predecessor TB-N1-A3 R1 hash bc016070 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A3 (2026-05-10; session #36; charter `handover/tracer_bullets/TB_N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_PHASE_2_charter_2026-05-10.md` §2 atom A3 + forward §8 grant `handover/directives/2026-05-10_TB_N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_PHASE_2_FORWARD_§8_GRANT.md`): threaded `action.stake_micro: Option<u64>` through the 3 OMEGA WorkTx-construction callsites (atom2 ~2329, atom3-omega-full ~2645, atom3-omega-pertactic ~3217). Each callsite now reads `action.stake_micro` first; if Some(u), uses that as i64; else falls back to the existing `TURINGOS_CHAINTAPE_PROPOSAL_STAKE_MICRO` env default (1000 μC). Closes the agency layer of CLAUDE.md §13: agent's `step` action carries an explicit per-tx stake within `[1, balance]` instead of the uniform env default. Pairs with sequencer step-4 admission gate + `TransitionError::StakeBalanceExceeded` tail-append to fail-closed reject `stake > balance` with distinct rejection-class telemetry. Predecessor TB-N1-A2 hash 60f41bc8 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY A2 (2026-05-10; session #35; preflight `handover/alignment/N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_LANDING_GAP_2026-05-10_session35.md`): replaced `let prompt_balance: f64 = ...` lookup at the per-tx prompt build site with `let econ_position: String = ... render_econ_position(&q, &agent_id) ...` invocation per A2 prompt-block landing. New helper at `src/sdk/econ_position.rs` reads canonical EconomicState (balances_t / stakes_t / claims_t / reputations_t) for the agent and returns a structured body that `build_agent_prompt` embeds under `=== Your Economic Position ===` heading. Closes session #35 smoke-evidence finding "n=1 economy structurally landed but invisible to agent at prompt layer" per CLAUDE.md §13 economy-laws + Art. III.2 progressive disclosure. Predecessor TB-18R Phase 2 hash 62834dff superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R Phase 2 (2026-05-06; preflight `handover/directives/2026-05-06_TB18R_PHASE_2_REMEDIATION_DIRECTIVE.md` §5): added typed `verdict_kind: Option<LeanVerdictKind>` field to `R2AttemptArgs` + threaded explicit kind through 6 emitter callsites (omega-full → Verified, omega-pertactic → Verified, step_partial_ok → PartialAccepted with `outcome: AttemptOutcome::PartialAccepted` replacing the LeanPass misnomer per FC-first analysis §2.5, step_reject → Failed, parse_fail → None (no LeanResult emitted), llm_err → None (no LeanResult emitted)); `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` constructs LeanResult with explicit verdict_kind or derives via `LeanResult::derive_verdict_kind_from_legacy_fields` if the emitter passes None. Closes architect ruling §5 Phase 2 typed-PartialAccepted requirement (parent ruling: `handover/directives/2026-05-06_TB18R_ROUND_2_ARCHITECT_RULING.md` §4 Q-P2; FC-first: `handover/directives/FC_FIRST_ANALYSIS_ASSERT45_PARTIAL_VERDICT_2026-05-06.md` §2.4 Option B). Predecessor TB-18R R3 hash 590070f0 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R3 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R3_STEP_B_admission.md §1.3 + charter SG-18R.2 + SG-18R.5): added file-scope async helper `r3_emit_failure_path_worktx` + wired 3 runtime-path failure WorkTx submissions (predicate_passes=false + stake=0 + proposal_cid=AttemptTelemetry CID) at evaluator paths step_reject (~3263) / parse_fail (~3275) / llm_err (~3289); each captures the AttemptTelemetry CID returned by R2's `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` and submits via `bus.submit_typed_tx`. Sequencer's R3 admission helper `refine_rejection_class_via_attempt_telemetry` reads AttemptTelemetry.outcome via WorkTx.proposal_cid and routes to L4.E with refined RejectionClass ∈ {LeanFailed=6, ParseFailed=7, SorryBlocked=8, LlmError=9}. step_partial_ok stays CAS-only per preflight §1.3 amended (LeanPass-on-rejection-arm would trip debug-build panic; intermediate L4 lane deferred to R5+). Class 3 wire-up depends on Class 4 R3.1 (RejectionClass tail-append) + R3.2 (sequencer admission) STEP_B-restricted surfaces. Omega paths NOT cut over per preflight §3.5 amended (TB-7 Gate 5 + audit_assertions id=24 walk L4 expecting WorkTx.proposal_cid → ProposalTelemetry; cutover would break audit chain). Predecessor TB-18R R2 hash 0ffb1e24 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R2 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R2_STEP_B_evaluator.md §1 + charter SG-18R.1): added per-LLM-call AttemptTelemetry CAS write at 6 evaluator paths (omega-full @ ~2317 / omega-pertactic @ ~2861 / step_partial_ok @ ~3236 / step_reject @ ~3263 / parse_fail @ ~3275 / llm_err @ ~3289) via new file-level `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` helper + `R2AttemptArgs` struct + `r2_prompt_ctx_hash` SHA-256 derivation (Cid::from_content cast per preflight §3.1 — no sha2 direct dep added to experiments/minif2f_v4/