rom `snap.price_index` + queries `prompt_balance` from `bus.sequencer.q_snapshot().economic_state_t.balances_t` (replaces legacy `snap.get_balance`; the `f64` is the `prompt.rs` render contract — `prompt.rs` is not a TB-14 module surface). (6) Boltzmann selector call replaced: `boltzmann_select_parent(&snap.tape, &prices, &params, &mut rng)` → `boltzmann_select_parent_v2(&snap.price_index, &snap.mask_set, &policy, &mut rng).map(|tx| tx.0)`. Predicate-blind (CR-14.1 + halt-trigger #1) — purely a scheduling priority pick. Predecessor TB-12 Atom 0.5(a) hash 8f1b97f1 superseded. (2026-05-03; architect 2026-05-03 ruling §1.1 + §8 Atom 0.5; TB-11 G3/G4 carry-forward closure): added 4 EvidenceCapsule counters (tb11_lean_error_count / tb11_sorry_block_count / tb11_protocol_parse_failure_count / tb11_partial_accept_count) instrumented at existing classify_lean_error / classify_parse_error / step_partial_ok call sites; sorry-block vs lean-error split via err_detail.contains("sorry") || err_detail.contains("forbidden_payload"); MAX_TX exhausted exit point (inside `if let Some(bundle) = chaintape_bundle`, BEFORE bundle.shutdown) now writes EvidenceCapsule to CAS via runtime::evidence_capsule::write_evidence_capsule + emits TerminalSummary on-chain via runtime::adapter::tb11_emit_terminal_summary_for_run with capsule_cid; bundle.shutdown drains the queued TerminalSummary tx via apply_one. Mirror of TB-8 tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify pattern. Predecessor TB-10 Atom 1+3 hash a5b30cd1 superseded.
